      "content": "Even if the discomfort feels manageable now, persistent redness and crusting after long screen sessions often indicate a need for more comprehensive care than just over-the-counter drops. Using artificial tears might temporarily relieve irritation but won't necessarily resolve the crusting caused by digital eye strain or potential underlying issues like blepharitis. Given the symptoms persisting overnight despite your relief, it is safer to consult a professional soon to prevent the condition from worsening rather than risking complications with self-treatment.",
